reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 29, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Works as expected
reviews.reviewText: Keyfobs programmed flawlessly with alfaobd. As a note, key in off position is what alfaobd calls “locked” also a rookie mistake on my part while testing remote start.Truck needs driver door unlocked, opened and then key inserted after remote start.If testing in driver seat remote starting the. Inserting the key, the truck will shut off immediately. Not a flaw, its a security function but it took me longer than it should have to catch onto this.All in all been using for a few months and they are working flawlessly.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 13, 2023
reviews.reviewText: I purchased these September of 2023. Had them programed and the keys cut at a Dodge dealership which costed another $100.00. Supposedly they had new batteries when purchased. Well on 11/12/2023 my truck showed low key fob battery. So I bought new batteries (CR2032) 3.0 Volt battery. I installed the battery, and went to the truck to make sure it was working and it will not work at all. Took it back apart and checked battery voltage and it had 3.01 volts. If I order a new key fob I will have to pay another $90.00 to get it programed. I would like a replacement. Will update after I find out what happens next.
